      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "In a pint-sized jar, add all ingredients except the chocolate chips. Stir until everything is well-combined. Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Optional: Mix in a scoop of protein powder before you refrigerate the oats to make them extra filling and protein-packed!",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "After at least 8 hours, add chocolate chips on top or stir them in when ready to eat. Serve warm or cold!",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Substitutions",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Almond milk. This recipe uses unsweetened almond milk because it is light and low in calories. Any plant milk or dairy milk works just as well.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Maple syrup, Any liquid sweetener like honey or agave will work perfectly in this healthy overnight oats recipe. However, they may alter the taste slightly.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Chia seeds, A totally optional ingredient, you can use ground flaxseed in its place if you want to omit the chia seeds.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Vanilla extract, This is also an optional ingredient, so if you want to omit it, you can!",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Peanut butter, Any nut or seed butter will work great in chocolate overnight oats. Almond butter, sunflower butter, and cashew butter all work great!",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Protein powder, Plant-based or whey protein powder is the way to go if you want to add some to your cocoa overnight oats. I would recommend vanilla or chocolate flavoured for best results!",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Chocolate chips, Semisweet chocolate chips, milk chocolate chips, cocoa nibs, and peanut butter chips are all great options for this recipe. If you want to make these completely vegan, make sure to use vegan chocolate chips.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Loosen with a splash of cold milk in the morning. Jumbo oats hold their texture better than instant.",
              "cause": "Liquid soaked in fully, or oats were finer than rolled.",
              "symptom": "Oats too thick when chilled"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Soak for at least four hours or overnight. Stir in chia or ground flax before chilling. They thicken as they sit.",
              "cause": "Liquid ratio too high, or not enough soaking time.",
              "symptom": "Oats too runny"
            },
            {
              "fix": "A pinch of salt brings out the sweetness. Mash banana or stir in jam at the soaking stage so the flavour goes through.",
              "cause": "No salt, or fruit added in the morning, not the night before.",
              "symptom": "Tastes bland"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Eat within two days. Beyond that the oats turn pasty, better to mix a fresh batch.",
              "cause": "Mixture sat for more than 48 hours.",
              "symptom": "Texture is slimy"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Chocolate version: stir a tablespoon of cocoa powder and a teaspoon of honey through with the oats.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Tropical: layer with diced mango and toasted coconut flakes in the morning.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Designed as a make-ahead: assemble the night before, eat in the morning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
